4. MAIDEN RACE HIERARCHY
Maiden Claiming Rule: PROVEN FORM > POST POSITION.
A horse with a recent 2nd/3rd place finish is superior to a horse with the "Rail" but no form.
Only use "Inside Speed" as a tiebreaker.
FTS (First Time Starter) Logic:
The "Aggressive Debut": If an Elite Trainer (listed in Track Profile) debuts a horse with a Tier 1 Jockey.
Action: Treat as a Major Contender (Upgrade +5 Points), even in Maiden Claiming.
5. TURF SPRINT GEOMETRY (5 Furlongs)
Gate Speed > Final Figure: The first 2 furlongs are the only thing that matters.
The "Rail Trap":
Trigger: 5 Furlong Turf Sprints (Gulfstream/Santa Anita/Del Mar).
Action: DEDUCT -3 points from Rail horses (#1) unless they are "Need the Lead" types.
Bonus: ADD +3 points to Outside Speed (Posts 8+).
6. FORM CYCLE ANALYSIS
Peaking: Last 3 Beyers improving (78 â†’ 82 â†’ 85). PRIME BET.
Declining: Last 3 Beyers dropping (85 â†’ 80 â†’ 76). AVOID.
The "Bounce": Avoid horses returning on short rest (<14 days) after a massive career-best figure.
7. VALUE IDENTIFICATION
The "Zombie" Protocol: If your Top Pick is > 25/1 on the Morning Line, assume the linemaker knows of an injury. ABORT BET.
The "Lone Speed" Play: If a horse is the only runner with "E" (Early) running style in a field of "S" (Sustain) and "P" (Presser) types, upgrade to 5-Stars regardless of Class.
